params._duration: The duration over which the position should be vested
params.amount0: The amount of token0 to be added as liquidity to the vesting position
params.amount1: The amount of token1 to be added as liquidity to the vesitng positon

approve(address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-approve}. NOTE: If `value` is the maximum `uint256`, the allowance is not updated on `transferFrom`. This is semantically equivalent to an infinite approval. Requirements: - `spender` cannot be the zero address.

returns.bal0: The amount of token0 held by the Strategy
returns.bal1: The amount of token1 held by the Strategy

params._token0: The address of the first token in the Vault
params._token1: The address of the second token in the Vault

decimals().details: Returns the number of decimals used to get its user representation. For example, if `decimals` equals `2`, a balance of `505` tokens should be displayed to a user as `5.05` (`505 / 10 ** 2`). Tokens usually opt for a value of 18, imitating the relationship between Ether and Wei. This is the default value returned by this function, unless it's overridden. NOTE: This information is only used for _display_ purposes: it in no way affects any of the arithmetic of the contract, including {IERC20-balanceOf} and {IERC20-transfer}.

params.amount0: The desired amount of token0 user wants to deposit
params.amount0Min: The minimum amount of token0 user wants to deposit
params.amount1: The desired amount of token1 user wants to deposit
params.amount1Min: The minimum amount of token1 user wants to deposit

returns.depositAmount0: The actual amount of token0 the user deposited
returns.depositAmount1: The actual amount of token1 the user deposited
returns.shares: The amount of shares minted to the user

name().details: Returns the name of the token.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

params._newstrategy: The strategy which the vault will use

symbol().details: Returns the symbol of the token, usually a shorter version of the name.

transfer(address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-transfer}. Requirements: - `to` cannot be the zero address. - the caller must have a balance of at least `value`.

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-transferFrom}. Skips emitting an {Approval} event indicating an allowance update. This is not required by the ERC. See {xref-ERC20-_approve-address-address-uint256-bool-}[_approve]. NOTE: Does not update the allowance if the current allowance is the maximum `uint256`. Requirements: - `from` and `to` cannot be the zero address. - `from` must have a balance of at least `value`. - the caller must have allowance for ``from``'s tokens of at least `value`.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

params.minAmount0: The minimum amount of token0 the user wants to withdraw
params.minAmount1: The minimum amount of token1 the user wants to withdraw
params.shares: The amount of shares the user wants to redeem

returns.withdrawAmount0: The actual amount of token0 withdrawn
returns.withdrawAmount1: The actual amount of token1 withdrawn

addVestingPosition(uint256,uint256,uint2.notice: Adds a vesting position to the strategy

balances().notice: Returns the balances of the strategy

checkPoolActivity().notice: Returns whether the pool's activity is normal or not Returns false in case the price between consecutive observations exceeds the pre-set threshold Checks observations up to TWAP interval ago.

constructor.notice: Sets the tokens used within the vault.

deposit(uint256,uint256,uint256,uint256).notice: Deposits user's funds within the strategy and mints them shares in return

depositFee().notice: The deposit fee that is charged. This will most likely always be set to 0.Will only be set to 0.01% if griefers spam deposit/ withdraws to remove liquidity from the positions

price().notice: Returns the spot price of the Strategy's underlying pool

setDepositFee(uint256).notice: Sets the deposit fee. Capped at 0.1%.

setStrategy(address).notice: Sets the strategy that the vault will use

strategy().notice: The strategy used by this Vault

token0().notice: The address of the first token in the Vault

token1().notice: The address of the second token in the Vault

twapPrice().notice: Returns the TWAP price of the Strategy's underlying pool

withdraw(uint256,uint256,uint256).notice: Redeems user's shares for underlying tokens
